# End-to-End Example Walkthrough

This section demonstrates a complete RCA execution flow from input bundle to final report.

---

# Example Scenario

A device support bundle contains:

- Ethernet failures
- WiFi client failures
- Kernel logs
- Network subsystem logs
- Multiple compressed archives

Example input:

```
sample_bundle.tgz
```

Contents:

```
sample_bundle.tgz

    |

    +-- device_logs.tar

            |

            +-- nvram2/

                    |

                    +-- log/

                            |

                            +-- kernel.log

                            +-- wifi.log

                            +-- messages.log
```

---

# Step 1: Run Analysis

Execute:

```bash
PYTHONPATH=src python3 -m app.main \
    --input sample_bundle.tgz \
    --output reports
```

---

# Step 2: Pipeline Execution

Console output:

```
2026-07-21 15:34:39 INFO Starting RCA pipeline


2026-07-21 15:34:39 INFO Extracted TAR sample_bundle.tgz


2026-07-21 15:34:39 INFO Scanning log directory:

reports/workspace/sample_bundle/nvram2/log


2026-07-21 15:34:39 INFO Discovered 108 log files


2026-07-21 15:34:39 INFO Detected 3089 events


2026-07-21 15:34:39 INFO Timeline created with 3089 events


2026-07-21 15:34:39 INFO Generating RCA report
```

---

# Step 3: Generated Output

The analyzer creates a timestamped execution directory.

Example:

```
reports/

└── 20260721_153439/

    |

    +-- metadata.json

    |

    +-- report.json

    |

    +-- summary.md

    |

    +-- workspace/

            |

            +-- sample_bundle/

                    |

                    +-- nvram2/

                            |

                            +-- log/
```

Each execution has an isolated workspace.

---

